adjective.description: Of, belonging to, or designating (part of) the Gulf of Bothnia or the lands surrounding it; = Bothnian.

origin: Early 17th century; earliest use found in Edward Grimeston (fl. 1604–1634), translator. From (i) French Bothnique and its probable etymon (ii) post-classical Latin Bothnicus from the name of Bothnia + -icus.
